header.gameNote: MID CONTINENT CONF TR IN TULSA OKLAHOMA

article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 83, UMKC 79
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Erik Kangas sank a late 3-pointer to cap a 12-point Oakland comeback and help the second-seeded Golden Grizzlies to an 83-79 win Monday over Missouri-Kansas City in the semifinal of the Mid-Continent Conference tournament. Oakland (19-13) will face top-seeded Oral Roberts in the championship game on Tuesday. Derick Nelson led the Golden Grizzlies with a career-high 23 points, including 15 in the second half. Kangas went 5-of-10 from three-point range and finished with 19 points. Quinton Day led the sixth-seeded Kangaroos (12-20) with 17 points, while Dee Ayuba and Tim Blackwell added 16 points apiece. Dane Brumagin sank two free throws with 1:26 left to give UMKC a 76-74 lead, but Kangas responded with a 3-pointer to put Oakland back on top. Day hit a late 3-pointer for the Kangaroos that cut the Oakland lead to 81-79, but Vova Severovas sealed the win for Oakland with two free throws with 9 seconds remaining. Oakland outrebounded UMKC 38-26, and Nelson led both teams with 10 rebounds. Oakland and Oral Roberts will meet in the championship game for the second time in three years.
